abstract: The police say a prominent New Jersey lawyer killed himself and his wife of 47 years. Their sons refuse to believe it.
snippet: The police say a prominent New Jersey lawyer killed himself and his wife of 47 years. Their sons refuse to believe it.
lead_paragraph: It was still dark, a half-hour until sunrise, when the fire trucks and police vehicles came wailing down country roads in central New Jersey and stopped in front of 49 Meadow Run Drive in Skillman, north of Princeton. The two-story, four-bedroom house sat on a one-acre lot in a 1970s-era subdivision that defines a kind of rustic suburbia. The back of the property was wooded, and there were still several farms nearby, some with fairly large herds of cattle.

abstract: This luxury performance sedan is, on average, 200 pounds lighter than the outgoing model, with a bonded and riveted aluminum platform instead of steel.
snippet: This luxury performance sedan is, on average, 200 pounds lighter than the outgoing model, with a bonded and riveted aluminum platform instead of steel.
lead_paragraph: BEFORE 2008, Jaguars with more than two doors had distinct designs as British as Highclere Castle. Then the XF arrived. Crisp and contemporary, it quickly became Jaguar’s best-selling car. Now, for its second generation, it has taken the approach that less is more.
headline_main: Video Review: The New XF, a Jaguar Light on Its Feet
headline_print_headline: A New Jaguar Light on Its Feet

abstract: The efforts in the halls of Congress are part of a multifront intervention by advocates for broader drone use as well as by their opponents, who argue that the machines pose significant safety and privacy risks.
snippet: The efforts in the halls of Congress are part of a multifront intervention by advocates for broader drone use as well as by their opponents, who argue that the machines pose significant safety and privacy risks.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The last time Congress weighed in on rules for nonmilitary drones, in 2012, the flying machines were hardly a hit with consumers. And companies said little about using them for commercial purposes.

abstract: House Democrats will huddle next week in Baltimore at a three-day strategy session that will include speeches by President Obama, Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and the comedian Trevor Noah.
snippet: House Democrats will huddle next week in Baltimore at a three-day strategy session that will include speeches by President Obama, Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and the comedian Trevor Noah.
lead_paragraph: Looking to chart a road map for the election year ahead, House Democrats will huddle next week in Baltimore at a three-day strategy session that will include speeches by President Obama, Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and the comedian Trevor Noah, the new host of “The Daily Show.”

abstract: The mogul’s purchase of the Plaza Hotel in 1988 offers insight into the methods and thinking of a deal maker turned presidential candidate.
snippet: The mogul’s purchase of the Plaza Hotel in 1988 offers insight into the methods and thinking of a deal maker turned presidential candidate.
lead_paragraph: The day Donald Trump called and asked for a one-on-one meeting in the winter of 1988, Tom Barrack was a relative newcomer to the high-stakes poker game of New York real estate. He had worked for nearly two years for Robert Bass, the Texas billionaire investor, and had played an important role in winning the Plaza Hotel for his boss the year before. Mr. Trump was the country’s most quotable and ostentatious financial celebrity, a guy with a jet, a 282-foot yacht and a fondness for peach-toned marble.

abstract: Banana Bag & Bodice’s new production at the Bushwick Starr owes a debt to Beckett but is exuberantly American.
snippet: Banana Bag & Bodice’s new production at the Bushwick Starr owes a debt to Beckett but is exuberantly American.
lead_paragraph: Mom is a mountain in “Longyarn,” the uninhibitedly shaggy new comedy from Banana Bag & Bodice. Her bedraggled head nearly scrapes the ceiling of the Bushwick Starr in Brooklyn, where Jason Craig’s play opened on Thursday night, and her scrawny torso is attached to a Brobdingnagian skirt that defies circumnavigation.

abstract: Tom Steyer, the billionaire environmental activist, will become one of the new chairmen for the Latino Victory Fund, along with Representative Joaquin Castro of Texas, Antonio Villaraigosa of Los Angeles and Melissa Mark-Viverito of New York.
snippet: Tom Steyer, the billionaire environmental activist, will become one of the new chairmen for the Latino Victory Fund, along with Representative Joaquin Castro of Texas, Antonio Villaraigosa of Los Angeles and Melissa Mark-Viverito of New York.
lead_paragraph: Tom Steyer, the billionaire environmental activist who invested heavily in the 2014 midterm elections, is joining forces with the Latino Victory Fund, the Democratic-leaning group that aims to elect Hispanics to higher office, a shift in approach for the 2016 elections.
